checkers.quals
Annotation Type Dependent

@Documented
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Dependent

Refines the qualified type of the annotated field or variable based on the qualified type of the receiver. The annotation declares a relationship between multiple type qualifier hierarchies.

Example: Consider a field, lock, that is only initialized if the enclosing object (the receiver), is marked as ThreadSafe. Such a field can be declared as: 


   private @Nullable @Dependent(result=NonNull.class, when=ThreadSafe.class)
     Lock lock;

Required Element Summary
Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
 Class<? extends Annotation> result
          The class of the refined qualifier to be applied.
 Class<? extends Annotation> when
          The qualifier class of the receiver that causes the result qualifier to be applied.
